4:
Kugui, you up? I made breakfast if
you're hungry.
7:
I'll leave it here in case you feel like
eating later.
21:
I should have known, the moment I
received the noise complaint...
23:
That I would find you two. Care to
explain what you are doing?
29:
While I appreciate your efforts to
comfort Kugui, I would ask that you
consider your methods more
carefully.
31:
This is the Diviner's
Commission—not a playground. We
have work that needs our attention,
without distractions—
35:
The Ama-no-Iwato strategy of
throwing a party outside didn't work,
huh... Hmm, what do we try next...
39:
By the by... Alk, why are you and your
companions still here?
43:
Well... We can't just go and abandon
a friend in need, can we?
45:
And... we figured we should try to
keep Ryouki in line, at least
somewhat.
49:
*sigh* So you do recognize that
you're running around without a
plan.
52:
What I cannot understand is why
you would go so far convincing
Kugui to return to painting.
54:
Wouldn't a true friend spare her the
pain and respect her decision?
60:
This isn't about friendship or
anything cheesy like that.
65:
It is not? But I thought for certain our
goal was to cheer her up!
69:
Er... Does that mean... you were just
harassing her for no reason this
whole time?
73: NO! Listen—Kugui is lying to herself!
76:
I KNOW she can still paint.
Somewhere deep inside, she WANTS
to.
78:
Denying herself like that... Well, I
can't stand it.
82:
What proof do you have that this is
the case?
86:
I don't have any, but I've just got a
gut feeling about this. Sounds crazy,
right? But I promise I wouldn’t make
this up—
96: Stella, thank you so, so much!
101: *sigh* Very well. I shall assist as well.
104:
Hindering your progress will only
result in more work for me, after all.
109:
You could just be honest and admit
that you care, you know?
112:
...I have an image to uphold, thank
you very much.
115:
Let us arrange a visit to Kugui's
village.
118:
We must ascertain the true nature
of that dragon, and learn more of
Kugui herself.
120:
Everyone, remain here while I
procure a map to lead us there.
126:
It's quiet... Have they finally lost
interest?
129:
It was only a matter of time. Without
my art, I am worthless.
132:
...I don't even know how to relax
without painting.
136:
I can't help myself, even after
everything that's happened... If only I
had never been born with this
power...
151: Kugui... We're going on a date.
163: Why are you still bothering with me?
165: I'm of no use to you if I can't paint.
168: Uh... Who do you take me for?
170:
It's not about what you can do for
ME—it's about what you can do for
yourself. I just can't stand to see you
like this.
177:
Yeah? Then explain why you
grabbed your brush and almost put
ink to paper.
180:
We're artists. We can't live if we don't
create.
182:
There's no escaping that fact. It's
who we are, through and through.
187: Then what do you suggest I do?
189:
It's either I quit, or I keep
endangering everyone around me!
Is that what you want?
193: Yep—so long as you're making art.
198:
Hey! We've got everything ready.
Here's the stuff you asked for.
207:
We've still got one stop left on this
date. You up for it?
212:
...I get the feeling I don't have a
choice. All right... Let's go.
